19 Kids and Counting star Michelle Duggar has revealed that she sticks to a $5 per person daily food budget in her bustling 20-person household.

The 47-year-old, who has nine daughters and ten sons ranging from three to 26 years old with her husband Jim Bob, 48, writes in her blog for TLC that she spends an average of $3,000 a month on groceries.

On her family's website she details some of the money-saving meals she likes to rustle up including Broccoli Casserole, Poor Man's Pizza and Three Bean Chilli.

