To save on shopping, Mrs Duggar says she shops for ingredients at discount stores, warehouse clubs and co-ops.

She mainly buys in bulk, stocking up once a month on staples including butter, cereal and oats.

She will return every three to four days to purchase fresh produce.

'You can save thousands of dollars by doing just that,' the devout Christian matriarch notes.

Although she maintains a close rein on the purse strings, Mrs Duggar says she used to be much stricter.

