Just a year ago she was spending around $2,000 every month on food.

However, higher food prices meant she had to up her spending. Growing children were another factor.

She humorously writes: 'Our boys have grown a lot and they have hollow legs. Josiah, Jedidiah, Jeremiah, and Jason are all tall and lanky.

'I jokingly say every two hours we have to fill up those hollow legs to make them grow a few more inches.'

When there are family get-togethers there are even more mouths to feed as Mr and Mrs Duggar also have three grandchildren, from their eldest son, Joshua, 26, who married Anna in September 2008 and moved out of home.

