Thanks to keeping a close eye on their finances the Duggars -  who will mark their 30th wedding anniversary this July - pride themselves on living debt free.

Along with watching what they eat, the couple shop for clothes at thrift stores, scour Craigslist for furniture, and have never brought a new car.

Mrs Duggar concludes: 'I'm willing to wait for a little bit to buy things we need. We've already decided we won't go into debt to buy things.

'If our couch wears out, I know I've got $65 to spend on a couch and we’ll look around.

